<p>I liked <a href="https://telegram.org">Telegram</a> since day 1 but after they released
their <strong>bot API</strong>, it became my favorite messaging app by far <sup id="fnref:1" role="doc-noteref"><a href="#fn:1" class="footnote" rel="footnote">1</a></sup>.</p>

<p>So, because <strong>I needed an excuse to learn Ruby</strong> (and also because I needed this
pretty bad) I created <a href="http://telegram.me/botzerra_bot">Botzerra_bot</a>:
my personal bot that queries latest news from my favorite feeds (theyâ€™re
mostly argentinian newspapers).</p>

<p>To use it, you just only have to look for <strong>botzerra_bot</strong> on Telegram (yeah,
like if youâ€™re searching for a contact). After that, you can send him <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">/start</code>
and follow the instructions for more information.</p>

